b'' b'| also, i seem to remember a posting saying that the scsi spec calls for' b'| foot between devices on the cable, but most cables you get (internal)' b"| don't meet the spec." b'|' b'| scsi ii draft proposal, rev. 10h, section single-ended' b'| cable, which is in the cable requirements section, has an' b'| implementor\'s note: stub clustering should be avoided. stubs' b'| should be spaced at least meters apart."' b'|' b'| for the non-technical, stubs are scsi devices. b'' b"however, also be aware that implementor's notes are basicly" b'recommendations, they are *not* part of the spec. as others have' b'noted, many vendors (including sgi) violate this. indeed, the main' b'point is to reduce impedance changes, and therefore reflections, and' b"therefore 'noise' on the bus." b'--' b'let no one tell me that silence gives consent, dave olson' b'because whoever is silent dissents. silicon graphics, inc.' 